{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH8EJrxPwWvTg7NyEeo5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. All 3 tests pass, including the new regression test.\n\n**The bug:** in `src/validate.js`, the domain regex used `(\\.[A-Za-z0-9-]*)*` — the `*` on the label body allowed an empty label, so `mail..example.com` matched (the second dot introduced a zero-length label). This contradicted the function's own doc comment (\"Labels must be NON-EMPTY\").\n\n**The fix:** changed that quantifier from `*` to `+`, requiring every domain label to have at least one character. Now `user@mail..example.com` is rejected, while normal addresses like `ada@example.com` and `mail.example.com` still pass.\n\nI also added a regression test for the consecutive-dots case, since the existing suite had never exercised it."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":324,"cache_read_input_tokens":24904,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":324},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c7c4f444-5c46-489c-866a-080e1e9f77a7","uuid":"651c888c-8370-49d1-b786-9fcb57112dda","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:50:52.506Z","request_id":"req_011CdH8EHqhLVz4uSh7LDU61"}
